    <title>Preferences - Proxy</title>
    <p>
        The following image displays the Proxy preferences dialog:
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <desc>The Proxy preferences dialog</desc>
        <media type="image" src="Images/preferences-proxy.png"/>
    </figure>
    
    <terms>
        <title>The following options are available:</title>
        <item>
            <title>Use a proxy for internet connectivity</title>
            <p>Enable this option and fill out the HTTP Proxy and port fields, if you want or have to connect to the internet via a proxy. The default port for many proxies is 8080.</p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Use authentication</title>
            <p>Some proxies need authentication before they can be used. Enable this option and fill out the "Usename" and "Password" fields, if that is the case.</p>
        </item>
    </terms>
</page>
